# Testing and verification — terminal use

## Quality gate (the **default** chained verification)

Full **quality gate** — ESLint, TypeScript, Stylelint, Vitest + coverage (**95%** all four v8 metrics: **`src-electron`**; **`helpers/**/*.ts`** **`unit-helpers`** instruments (**`helpers/playwrightHelpers_*`** excluded); scoped **`i18n/`** (**`unit-i18n`**); renderer **`src`** **`.ts`** (**`unit-src-renderer`**); **`.ts`** under **`src/components`**, **`src/layouts`**, **`src/pages`** (**`unit-components`**); **`.vue`** SFCs **~60%** watermarks only) — **one** terminal invocation. Prefer **`yarn testbatch:verify`** in `package.json` (same steps, stops first failure):

`yarn testbatch:verify`

**Yarn 1.x**: do **not** use `yarn check` — built-in validates dependency tree, not this script.

Equivalent chain: `yarn lint:eslint && yarn lint:typescript && yarn lint:stylelint && yarn test:coverage:verify`

**Faster** unit pass without coverage: **`yarn test:unit`** (electron, **`src`** TS, helpers, **`i18n`**, components) while iterating; **never** treat as end-of-edits gate.

## End of code edits (agents) — mandatory

Substantive source edits in a turn → **last verification action** before done summary:

1. **`yarn testbatch:verify`** — one terminal, full chain ([dev-electron-compile-check.mdc](dev-electron-compile-check.mdc)).
2. Dev Electron compile smoke — second terminal, same rule.

- **Any edit after step 1 passed** → step 1 **invalid**; re-run on current tree.
- **Do not** report “done” / “shipped” / “fixed” without Shell **`yarn testbatch:verify`** on final tree.
- Slice commands (`yarn eslint <path>`, `vitest run <spec>`, partial stylelint) = debug while editing only — [dev-electron-compile-check.mdc](dev-electron-compile-check.mdc) **Does not satisfy step 1**.

Same **`testbatch:verify`** as commit gate; do not skip because dev is already running. Finish **`yarn testbatch:verify`** before commits **and** before reporting substantive agent work done.

**Beyond default gate:** discover + run connected **Playwright** component + **E2E** specs (grep dialog name, **`data-test-locator`**, locale default export, action id). **`yarn testbatch:verify`** does **not** include those. [fantasia-testing](../skills/fantasia-testing/SKILL.md) **Connected tests for any feature change**.

**Changelog-only exception** (rare): **only** files to commit = locale changelog Markdown **`i18n/*/documents/changeLog.md`** **and** **`yarn testbatch:verify` already passed** after last substantive edits with **no** other uncommitted changes → may **skip** gate immediately before that commit. **Default**: changelog in **same commit** as substantive work (before push), not separate changelog commit after batch/push. **Uncertain** (mixed edits, parallel work, unsure gate ran on current tree) → run **`yarn testbatch:verify`**.

**Exception**: **debugging** specific failing step → run command **alone** (+ narrower follow-ups) until pass, then full chained gate before commit/changelog (unless changelog-only above).

By default do not extend chain with `yarn quasar:build:electron`, Playwright, or Storybook.

Post-implementation agent gates (order): **`yarn testbatch:verify`** then dev compile smoke — [dev-electron-compile-check.mdc](dev-electron-compile-check.mdc). Dev step alone is **not** the quality gate.

## Full-suite gates (`testbatch:ensure:nochange` / `testbatch:ensure:change`)

Explicit full project gate in one command:

- **`yarn testbatch:ensure:nochange`** — `testbatch:verify`, **`yarn quasar:build:electron:summarized`** (Quasar/electron-builder output; success one line; failure full log — default **`test-results/quasar-build-electron-last.log`**, gitignored with **`test-results/`**), Playwright component + E2E, **`yarn test:storybook:smoke`**, **`yarn test:storybook:visual`** (committed VRT snapshots; fails on drift). **`yarn test:storybook:visual`** also fails when story iframe has neither element children under **`#storybook-root`** nor **`#root`** nor visible portaled dialog/menu chrome after waiter (mount ids inspected separately — not only first **`querySelector('#storybook-root, #root')`**) unless **`tags: ['skip-visual-render-check']`** or **id** in **`EXCLUDED_STORY_IDS`** in **`.storybook-workspace/visual-tests/storybook.visual.playwright.test.ts`**. **`yarn test:storybook:visual`** fails only on **GitHub** **`windows-latest`** with **`toHaveScreenshot`** pixel counts just above **`maxDiffPixels`** → **README** **Storybook visual baseline policy** (**`maxDiffPixels`** = whole-image differing-pixel cap, not width).
- **`yarn testbatch:ensure:change`** — same through E2E + smoke, then **`yarn test:storybook:visual:update`** for intentional UI baseline refresh. Use only when UI changes approved + commit updated snapshots.

Intentional exception to isolation rule. **Do not** run **`testbatch:ensure:change`** in CI or validate unchanged baseline.

Default **GitHub Actions** **Verify** (`.github/workflows/verify.yml`) runs **`yarn testbatch:verify`** only — not Storybook smoke/visual, Electron production build, Playwright component/E2E. Run **`yarn test:storybook:visual`** / **`yarn testbatch:ensure:nochange`** locally for VRT.

## Everything else — one command per terminal

Each in **own** terminal (no chain with each other or quality gate) unless **`yarn testbatch:ensure:nochange`** or **`yarn testbatch:ensure:change`**:

- `yarn quasar:build:electron` (full build log; streaming output)
- `yarn test:components`
- `yarn test:e2e`
- `yarn test:storybook:smoke`
- `yarn test:storybook:visual` / `yarn test:storybook:visual:update` (and other `test:storybook:visual*` variants)

Isolated logs → easier failure triage.

**Playwright Electron `userData`:** Component/E2E set `TEST_ENV`; main uses **`%APPDATA%/<package.json name>/playwright-user-data`** (repo: **`Roaming\fantasia-archive\playwright-user-data`**), **not** **`fantasia-archive-dev`**. Specs: **`test.describe.serial`**; each group **`test.beforeAll`** **`await`**s **`launchFaPlaywrightComponentHarnessWindow`** / **`launchFaPlaywrightE2eAppWindow`**, which run **`resetFaPlaywrightIsolatedUserData()`** from **`helpers/playwrightHelpers_universal/playwrightUserDataReset.ts`** before **`electron.launch`**. See **`src-electron/mainScripts/appIdentity/appIdentity_manager.ts`**, **`playwrightIsolatedUserDataDirName.ts`**, [playwright-tests.mdc](playwright-tests.mdc).

**Playwright `keyboard.press` (cross-OS keybinds):** Component/E2E driving global shortcuts or keybind capture must match app **primary** (Command macOS, Control Windows/Linux) vs **literal Control** in saved overrides. **`helpers/playwrightHelpers_universal/faPlaywrightKeyboardChords.ts`** + **Keyboard strings** in [playwright-tests.mdc](playwright-tests.mdc); [fantasia-testing](../skills/fantasia-testing/SKILL.md) **Playwright keyboard.press and app keybinds**.

## Reporting

Report progress in execution order. On substantive work: **end with verify gate result** (pass/fail from **`yarn testbatch:verify`** on current tree) — [dev-electron-compile-check.mdc](dev-electron-compile-check.mdc).
